cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically edge detection and semantic segmentation. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel deep learning architecture, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the use of ResNet and multi-label loss function indicates that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
